HEADWORD: Arquebusier
<hw>Ar`que*bus*ier</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>arquebusier</ets>.]</ety> <def>A soldier armed with an
arquebus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Soldiers armed with guns, of whatsoever sort or denomination,
appear to have been called <qex>arquebusiers</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>E.
Lodge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Arquifoux</ent>⟦br⟧
